00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:28,280
Cosine theta plus phi.

65
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:31,280
Right. Cosine of theta plus phi.

66
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:35,280
That's, sorry, that's the high school trigonometry formula.

67
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,780
The cosine of the sum of two

68
00:03:37,780 --> 00:03:40,280
angles, cosine cosine minus sine times sine.

69
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:44,780
And then, plus the imaginary part, and the imaginary part

70
00:03:44,780 --> 00:03:49,280
is cosine theta sine phi plus cosine phi times sine theta,

71
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:53,280
and that's just sine of theta plus phi.

72
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,780
And by definition, if e to the

73
00:03:55,780 --> 00:03:58,280
i theta is cosine plus i sine,

74
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,780
then this is just cosine, then this is

